@email = tenant.{{$guid}}@example.com
@password = Passw0rd123

### Register a fresh org for this run (self-contained — doesn't depend on auth.http)
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Tenant",
  "lastName": "Tester",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "organizationName": "Tenant Http Org"
}

### Current tenant — status PENDING right after register
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/tenants/me

### Update organization settings (Owner has the organization.update permission)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/tenants/me
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "industry": "Software",
  "size": "SMALL"
}

### List members — should show just the Owner (this user)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/tenants/me/members

### [dev/test only] fetch the verification token
# @name verificationToken
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/verification-token?email={{email}}

### Verify email — PENDING -> TRIALING (also fires provisioning for pending subscriptions)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{verificationToken.response.body.$.data.token}}"
}

### Confirm status is now TRIALING with trialEndsAt set
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/tenants/me

### Invalid transition check — cancelling twice should 409 the second time (run this request twice)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/tenants/me/cancel

### Confirm tenant endpoints now 403 with a TENANT_CANCELLED code
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/tenants/me
